#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.97"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.97:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.97:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga"
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.97:0.3"
msgid "97. Dutiyaājānīyasutta"
msgstr "97. The Thoroughbred (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.97:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti "
"rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhayaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with three factors is worthy of a "
"king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship."

msgctxt "an3.97:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.97:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhadro assājānīyo vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno "
"ca javasampanno ca."
msgstr "It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is beautiful, strong, and fast."

msgctxt "an3.97:1.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo "
"rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"A fine royal thoroughbred with these three factors is worthy of a king, …"

msgctxt "an3.97:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … "
"pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant with three factors is worthy of offerings "
"dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s "
"offering, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field "
"of merit for the world."

msgctxt "an3.97:1.6"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.97:1.7"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno ca javasampanno "
"ca."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is beautiful, strong, and fast."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.97:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant beautiful?"

msgctxt "an3.97:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.97:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is beautiful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.97:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant strong?"

msgctxt "an3.97:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful "
"qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They are strong, staunchly "
"vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an3.97:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is strong."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.97:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant fast?"

msgctxt "an3.97:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn "
"spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from "
"that world."

msgctxt "an3.97:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is fast."

msgctxt "an3.97:4.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … "
"anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these three factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the "
"world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.97:4.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
